WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.667 line:80%
Entrepreneurs get comfortable with risk by learning to
differentiate between impulsive risk and calculated risk.

00:00:07.397 --> 00:00:12.769 line:80%
Successful entrepreneurs calculate costs and benefits before making a 
risky decision.

00:00:13.271 --> 00:00:16.075 line:80%
Alejandra wants to open her own boutique.

00:00:16.379 --> 00:00:19.533 line:80%
She has found a location for her shop on a busy street.

00:00:20.077 --> 00:00:22.616 line:80%
However, the rent is higher than her budget.

00:00:22.640 --> 00:00:30.533 line:80%
If Alejandra decides to rent the shop simply because she likes the locality,
 it would be an impulsive risk that may not work out.

00:00:31.091 --> 00:00:35.537 line:80%
However, Alejandra sees the potential in setting up her shop on a busy street.

00:00:36.188 --> 00:00:41.292 line:80%
She anticipates that the increase in walk-in customers is likely to 
cover the steep rent.

00:00:41.818 --> 00:00:48.464 line:80%
 After carefully analyzing the costs and benefits,
 she takes a calculated risk by deciding to rent the shop.